<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870316-0164 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:3COM Corp.</HL><DD> 03/16/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> COMSSTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><TEXT>   3COM CORP. said it is offering 1.2 million common shares at $23.50 each. The Santa Clara, Calif.-based maker of equipment that connects personal computers into networks said proceeds of the offering will be used for working capital. Goldman, Sachs andamp; Co. is managing the offering. Prior to the offering, 3Com had about 14.2 million shares outstanding. In over-the-counter trading Friday, the company's common shares closed at $23.25, down 37.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>